1
00:00:01,041 --> 00:00:05,083
[upbeat theme music plays]

2
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:07,333
<i>♪ You never do know</i>
<i>what's around the bend ♪</i>

3
00:00:07,416 --> 00:00:09,250
<i>♪ Big adventure</i>
<i>or a brand-new friend ♪</i>

4
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:10,916
<i>♪ When you're curious ♪</i>

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,791
<i>-♪ Like Curious George ♪</i>
-[chorus] Swing!

6
00:00:13,875 --> 00:00:15,833
<i>-♪ Well, now, every day ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Every day ♪</i>

7
00:00:15,916 --> 00:00:17,791
<i>-♪ Is so glorious ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Glorious ♪</i>

8
00:00:17,875 --> 00:00:19,416
-George.
-<i>♪ And everything ♪</i>

9
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,333
[chorus]<i> ♪ Everything ♪</i>

10
00:00:20,416 --> 00:00:22,625
<i>-♪ Is so wondrous ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Wondrous ♪</i>

11
00:00:22,708 --> 00:00:26,791
<i>♪ There's more to explore</i>
<i>when you open your door ♪</i>

12
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,375
<i>♪ And meet friends like this ♪</i>

13
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:31,416
<i>-♪ You just can't miss ♪</i>
-[chorus] Whoa!

14
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,541
<i>-♪ I get curious ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Curious ♪</i>

15
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:35,791
<i>-♪ And that's marvelous ♪</i>
-[chorus]<i> ♪ Marvelous ♪</i>

16
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:37,916
<i>♪ And that's your reward ♪</i>

17
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,916
<i>♪ You'll never be bored ♪</i>

18
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,416
<i>♪ If you ask yourself,</i>
<i>"What is this?" ♪</i>

19
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,416
<i>♪ Like Curious ♪</i>

20
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:48,375
<i>♪ Like Curious,</i>
<i>Curious George ♪</i>

21
00:00:48,458 --> 00:00:49,458
Oh.

22
00:00:50,708 --> 00:00:57,541
<i>♪♪</i>

23
00:00:59,666 --> 00:01:02,291
[chattering happily]

24
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:05,125
[narrator]<i> George loved</i>
<i>visiting the Renkin's farm,</i>

25
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:07,416
<i>because there was always</i>
<i>something new to see.</i>

26
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:10,500
[chattering cheerfully]

27
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:17,500
[narrator] <i>And in Spring, there</i>
<i>were even more new things.</i>

28
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:20,583
-[chuckles]
-[cow moos]

29
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:23,250
Yep, Leslie had a new calf.

30
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,833
And she wasn't the only one!

31
00:01:25,916 --> 00:01:28,333
Gertie had a kid.

32
00:01:28,416 --> 00:01:30,833
[coos softly]

33
00:01:30,916 --> 00:01:34,250
And Pearl had
a litter of piglets.

34
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:37,333
[pigs snort and squeal]

35
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:45,500
[chatters sadly]

36
00:01:45,583 --> 00:01:48,708
Oh, that's Hamilton.
He's the runt of the litter.

37
00:01:48,791 --> 00:01:50,541
[jabbering in confusion]

38
00:01:50,625 --> 00:01:52,583
The runt is
the smallest one, George.

39
00:01:52,666 --> 00:01:57,125
He'll need special care
until he's a little bigger.

40
00:01:57,208 --> 00:02:00,125
 [playful piano music]

41
00:02:00,208 --> 00:02:03,208
<i>♪♪</i>

42
00:02:03,291 --> 00:02:05,875
[coos]

43
00:02:05,958 --> 00:02:09,458
[chatters helpfully]

44
00:02:10,291 --> 00:02:12,875
You want to
take care of Hamilton?

45
00:02:12,958 --> 00:02:15,333
[chatters happily]

46
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:17,708
George, taking care
of a little piglet

47
00:02:17,791 --> 00:02:19,708
is a big responsibility.

48
00:02:19,791 --> 00:02:22,875
How about you help me plant
these gladiola bulbs instead?

49
00:02:22,958 --> 00:02:24,583
 [melancholy piano music]

50
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:26,250
[groans]

51
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:29,375
Now, you want to plant
these four inches deep.

52
00:02:29,458 --> 00:02:32,375
[playful piano music]

53
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:34,375
[squealing]

54
00:02:34,458 --> 00:02:37,416
[cries worriedly]

55
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,833
[chattering]

56
00:02:39,916 --> 00:02:42,750
[squealing]

57
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:46,375
Wow, that little pig
sure is fast!

58
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:49,291
Thank goodness
George stopped him.

59
00:02:49,375 --> 00:02:51,625
[chatters]

60
00:02:51,708 --> 00:02:54,500
<i>♪♪</i>

61
00:02:54,583 --> 00:02:59,583
Okay, I guess Hamilton comes
home with us for a while.

62
00:02:59,666 --> 00:03:02,375
[chatters triumphantly]

63
00:03:02,458 --> 00:03:04,708
I'll get you some supplies
and make a list

64
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:08,250
of all the things you'll have
to do to take care of Hamilton.

65
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:10,458
First, you're going
to have to feed him

66
00:03:10,541 --> 00:03:12,500
four times a day.

67
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:14,791
-[chatters]
-[snorting]

68
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:17,458
[narrator] <i>George tried</i>
<i>to listen to Farmer Renkins.</i>

69
00:03:17,541 --> 00:03:19,833
You'll need a warm blanket.

70
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:22,375
[narrator] <i>But he couldn't help</i>
<i>dreaming of all the fun</i>

71
00:03:22,458 --> 00:03:24,291
<i>he and his little buddy</i>
<i>would have.</i>

72
00:03:24,375 --> 00:03:25,916
You want to give him a bath.

73
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,541
 [jazz music]

74
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:29,916
[sighs]

75
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:31,625
[cheerful jazz music]

76
00:03:31,708 --> 00:03:34,041
[snorting]

77
00:03:34,125 --> 00:03:35,958
Here's the list of
directions from Mr. Renkins.

78
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:38,625
Don't want to lose this.

79
00:03:38,708 --> 00:03:42,291
<i>♪♪</i>

80
00:03:42,375 --> 00:03:44,916
Everything Hamilton needs
is in the sack.

81
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,791
I'm gonna take these bulbs
to the garden.

82
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:48,625
[giggles]

83
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:50,833
Holler if you need anything.

84
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,625
[chattering happily]

85
00:03:52,708 --> 00:03:55,833
[snorting]

86
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:58,375
[narrator]
<i>Hamilton must be hungry.</i>

87
00:03:58,458 --> 00:04:02,291
<i>Feeding him would be George's</i>
<i>first piglet care task.</i>

88
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,833
[rumbling]

89
00:04:03,916 --> 00:04:06,458
<i>And George</i>
<i>would feed himself too.</i>

90
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:09,458
<i>♪♪</i>

91
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:12,625
<i>Why was Hamilton so squealy?</i>

92
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:15,708
[squealing]

93
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,833
<i>♪♪</i>

94
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:25,750
<i>He probably</i>
<i>just wanted a better seat.</i>

95
00:04:27,375 --> 00:04:29,833
[snorting]

96
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:35,041
<i>Who didn't like a peanut</i>
<i>butter, jelly, banana,</i>

97
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:37,833
<i>and carrot sandwich?</i>

98
00:04:37,916 --> 00:04:39,583
[gasps]

99
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:42,541
[narrator]
<i>Hamilton, that was who.</i>

100
00:04:42,625 --> 00:04:45,500
<i>Maybe he just</i>
<i>needed a little help.</i>

101
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:48,500
[chattering happily]

102
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:50,375
<i>♪♪</i>

103
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,958
[snorting]

104
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:55,333
[cries]

105
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:57,500
[narrator] <i>Feeding a piglet</i>
<i>required patience.</i>

106
00:04:57,583 --> 00:04:59,833
[clattering]

107
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:02,833
[playful marimba music]

108
00:05:02,916 --> 00:05:05,375
[snorting]

109
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,833
[chattering worriedly]

110
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:12,541
♪♪

111
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:13,958
Hi, George.

112
00:05:14,375 --> 00:05:16,916
Huh? How'd you get up there?

113
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,083
You hungry, Hamilton?

114
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:22,833
[snorting]

115
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:25,208
[chattering inquisitively]

116
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:28,000
This bottle?
This is Hamilton's food.

117
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:30,875
[chattering happily]

118
00:05:30,958 --> 00:05:33,083
[narrator]
<i>Who knew it was so easy?</i>

119
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:35,208
[chattering happily]

120
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:37,375
You sure you can feed him?

121
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:39,083
[chattering happily]

122
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:41,041
Okay, here you go.

123
00:05:41,125 --> 00:05:44,125
[coos]

124
00:05:45,791 --> 00:05:48,083
[narrator] <i>After lunch,</i>
<i>George was ready</i>

125
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:50,166
<i>to give Hamilton some exercise.</i>

126
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:52,208
[grunting happily]

127
00:05:52,291 --> 00:05:54,791
[chattering happily]

128
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:57,833
[squealing]

129
00:05:57,916 --> 00:06:00,833
[chattering worriedly]

130
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:03,791
[narrator] <i>Well, at least one</i>
<i>of them would get exercise.</i>

131
00:06:03,875 --> 00:06:06,791
 [cheerful marimba music]

132
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:13,875
<i>♪♪</i>

133
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,041
[chattering in confusion]

134
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:22,291
[chewing]

135
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:26,958
<i>♪♪</i>

136
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:28,708
[chattering questioningly]

137
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:33,250
Well, Hamilton uprooted
all my gladiola bulbs.

138
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:36,333
[unsure chattering]

139
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:40,500
Pigs like to dig things
out of the ground.

140
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:43,375
How about you two play
in the front yard?

141
00:06:43,458 --> 00:06:46,375
[chattering happily]

142
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:49,375
[cheerful marimba music]

143
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:53,000
<i>♪♪</i>

144
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:55,333
[groans]

145
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:58,291
[narrator] <i>Maybe soccer just</i>
<i>wasn't Hamilton's game.</i>

146
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,416
Luckily,
George knew plenty of others.

147
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,000
[chattering happily]

148
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:09,000
[giggling]

149
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,250
[coos]

150
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,791
[groans]

151
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:17,958
[cheerful flute music]

152
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:20,791
[chattering happily]

153
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:23,041
[snorting]

154
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:26,125
[spitting and gasping]

155
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:29,208
[snorting]

156
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,375
[narrator] <i>George was ready</i>
<i>for his very first</i>

157
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:33,166
<i>Hamilton sleepover.</i>

158
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:36,000
[squealing]

159
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:37,541
[snorting]

160
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:39,791
[whines]

161
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:43,166
You know, George, not every
animal likes to be picked up

162
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,791
like a little monkey.

163
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:47,125
[chattering in confusion]

164
00:07:47,208 --> 00:07:48,541
Yeah.

165
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:50,250
Maybe we should make
him a bed down here

166
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:52,375
so we don't have
to carry him upstairs.

167
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:55,041
[whines]

168
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:58,041
 [sleepy piano music]

169
00:07:58,125 --> 00:08:00,541
[snorting]

170
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,166
<i>♪♪</i>

171
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:04,166
Say good night, George.

172
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:07,250
[coos]

173
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,458
Don't worry, George.

174
00:08:09,541 --> 00:08:12,041
You can have more fun
with Hamilton tomorrow.

175
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:15,125
[coos]

176
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:18,583
[narrator] <i>But George didn't</i>
<i>really have fun with Hamilton.</i>

177
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:22,166
<i>And now, they weren't</i>
<i>even having a sleepover.</i>

178
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:25,166
[bluesy piano music]

179
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:28,083
<i>♪♪</i>

180
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:31,083
<i>George wondered</i>
<i>why the day hadn't gone better.</i>

181
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:33,375
[hooting]

182
00:08:33,457 --> 00:08:36,166
<i>♪♪</i>

183
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:39,916
<i>But there were a lot of things</i>
<i>George wondered about.</i>

184
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,457
<i>Like how those baby owls</i>

185
00:08:42,541 --> 00:08:44,500
<i>could eat a worm.</i>

186
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,375
Ew!

187
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:51,041
<i>♪♪</i>

188
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:54,291
<i>Owls must just be different</i>
<i>than monkeys.</i>

189
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:57,166
[chattering happily]

190
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:59,291
[narrator] <i>Maybe that was it.</i>

191
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:02,625
<i>George was caring for Hamilton</i>
<i>like he was a little monkey,</i>

192
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:05,166
<i>instead of a little pig.</i>

193
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,625
[squealing]

194
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:09,416
[chattering in concern]

195
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,291
[chattering]

196
00:09:11,375 --> 00:09:14,333
[squealing]

197
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:16,500
[coos]

198
00:09:16,583 --> 00:09:18,166
[narrator]
<i>George remembered that Hamilton</i>

199
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,625
<i>liked drinking from a bottle.</i>

200
00:09:19,708 --> 00:09:21,958
[squealing]

201
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,958
[coos]

202
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:28,375
[squealing]

203
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:31,250
[narrator]<i> Nope, not hungry.</i>

204
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:33,083
[whines]

205
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,916
[narrator]<i> George wished</i>
<i>he knew what Hamilton wanted.</i>

206
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,666
[chattering happily]

207
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,375
[narrator] <i>Mr. Rankin's list!</i>

208
00:09:39,458 --> 00:09:41,375
<i>Maybe that had the answer.</i>

209
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:44,416
[snorting]

210
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,500
[coos]

211
00:09:48,583 --> 00:09:50,666
[narrator]<i> That was the problem.</i>

212
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:54,125
<i>Little pigs liked</i>
<i>to be cozy and warm!</i>

213
00:09:54,208 --> 00:09:56,458
[chattering happily]

214
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:59,333
[snorting]

215
00:09:59,416 --> 00:10:01,000
[narrator]<i> It worked.</i>

216
00:10:01,083 --> 00:10:04,208
[coos]

217
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,541
[narrator]<i> George finally slept,</i>

218
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:09,166
<i>thinking of all the fun he and</i>
<i>Hamilton would have together</i>

219
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,708
<i>tomorrow, little piggy style.</i>

220
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:14,708
 [soft piano music]

221
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:16,208
<i>♪♪</i>

222
00:10:16,291 --> 00:10:19,208
[cheerful music]

223
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:26,291
<i>♪♪</i>

224
00:10:42,625 --> 00:10:46,166
[chattering happily]

225
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:47,750
[narrator]
<i>Before George knew it,</i>

226
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,333
<i>Hamilton was big and strong,</i>

227
00:10:50,916 --> 00:10:53,083
<i>and it was time</i>
<i>to take him home.</i>

228
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:57,500
Ha! You did a fine job
raising Hamilton, George.

229
00:10:57,583 --> 00:11:00,625
Now we just have to see
if his brothers and sisters

230
00:11:00,708 --> 00:11:02,416
will accept him.

231
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,125
[cheerful piano music]

232
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:06,125
[chattering nervously]

233
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:09,125
[snorting]

234
00:11:09,208 --> 00:11:14,083
<i>♪♪</i>

235
00:11:14,166 --> 00:11:16,666
[squealing]

236
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:23,750
<i>♪♪</i>

237
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:27,166
-[chattering happily]
-Yay!

238
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,583
[narrator]<i> George had done it.</i>

239
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:30,750
<i>He had raised a pig.</i>

240
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:33,125
Okay, George.
Time to go.

241
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:35,625
[coos]

242
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:38,125
[snorting]

243
00:11:38,208 --> 00:11:39,750
[whines]

244
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:42,166
[narrator] <i>Had Hamilton</i>
<i>forgotten George?</i>

245
00:11:44,541 --> 00:11:46,541
[snorting]

246
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:49,333
[squealing]

247
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:51,083
[chattering happily]

248
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:52,625
[narrator] <i>Not a chance.</i>

249
00:11:52,708 --> 00:11:55,708
[coos]

250
00:11:58,916 --> 00:12:01,833
[ominous marimba music]

251
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:04,708
<i>♪♪</i>

252
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,041
[narrator] <i>George was excited</i>

253
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:08,625
<i>to try out</i>
<i>his brand new watercolors.</i>

254
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:10,166
[grunts]

255
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:12,083
Time for bed, George!

256
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:14,791
Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to startle you.

257
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:16,750
<i>♪♪</i>

258
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,416
There, it's still okay.

259
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:21,083
[chatters gloomily]

260
00:12:21,166 --> 00:12:24,083
[soft piano music]

261
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:26,875
<i>♪♪</i>

262
00:12:26,958 --> 00:12:28,416
Sleep well.

263
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,208
Tomorrow, we're going
to the park with Hundley.

264
00:12:31,291 --> 00:12:34,208
[sighs]

265
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:35,916
<i>♪♪</i>

266
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,208
Nighty-night.

267
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,416
[sighs]

268
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,250
 [dreamy music]

269
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:44,250
[laughing]

270
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:45,750
[panting]

271
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,333
[chattering happily]

272
00:12:47,416 --> 00:12:49,750
[barking]

273
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,291
[cheerful music]

274
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:52,958
[growling]

275
00:12:53,041 --> 00:12:55,791
[chattering in curiosity]

276
00:12:58,416 --> 00:13:01,291
[gasps]

277
00:13:01,375 --> 00:13:03,125
[narrator] <i>George had never seen</i>

278
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:06,041
<i>a green rhino</i>
<i>in the park before.</i>

279
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:08,125
[screams]

280
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:10,958
[tense music]

281
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:12,333
[snorting]

282
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:15,125
[screams]

283
00:13:15,208 --> 00:13:18,041
<i>♪♪</i>

284
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:21,791
Bad rhino!
You bring that back!

285
00:13:21,875 --> 00:13:23,791
[grunts in confusion]

286
00:13:23,875 --> 00:13:28,750
♪♪

287
00:13:30,208 --> 00:13:32,333
[barking]

288
00:13:32,416 --> 00:13:33,958
[chattering in confusion]

289
00:13:34,083 --> 00:13:36,041
[barking]

290
00:13:36,125 --> 00:13:40,500
[chattering happily]

291
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:42,750
[barks]

292
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:45,875
[chattering happily]

293
00:13:45,958 --> 00:13:48,958
[screaming]

294
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:51,916
[screaming]

295
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,083
[gasping]

296
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:55,166
George!

297
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,875
Are you all right?

298
00:13:56,958 --> 00:13:58,416
[coos]

299
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:01,500
[chattering nervously]

300
00:14:03,916 --> 00:14:06,291
[grunting angrily]

301
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:09,750
[cawing]

302
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:13,875
You saw that rhino
and a flying dog?

303
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:16,958
[chattering nervously]

304
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,458
Oh, it sounds
like a nightmare.

305
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:22,250
[coos in confusion]

306
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,041
It's a scary dream.

307
00:14:24,125 --> 00:14:26,208
Dreams are stories in your head

308
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:28,541
and we call the scary dreams
nightmares.

309
00:14:28,625 --> 00:14:30,208
But they aren't real.

310
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:32,500
[whimpering]

311
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:35,916
[narrator]
<i>It sure seemed real to George.</i>

312
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,333
[playful marimba music]

313
00:14:37,416 --> 00:14:39,875
<i>But the Man</i>
<i>didn't have a horn now.</i>

314
00:14:39,958 --> 00:14:41,875
Were you dreaming of me too?

315
00:14:41,958 --> 00:14:43,458
[whimpers]

316
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:47,791
Well when you wake up,
and see your bed and your room,

317
00:14:47,875 --> 00:14:50,291
you know you're safe
and everything is okay.

318
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:52,375
See?

319
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:55,416
[soft marimba music]

320
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:57,250
<i>♪♪</i>

321
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:59,291
Hey, there's Hundley.

322
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:01,541
[quacking]

323
00:15:01,625 --> 00:15:04,833
[chattering nervously]

324
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:07,125
[barking]

325
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:10,291
Ahh, so it was Hundley who
was flying in your dream.

326
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:12,958
George had a nightmare
last night.

327
00:15:13,041 --> 00:15:15,583
Oh, I once had one
where the mailman

328
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:17,291
delivered a box of mice!

329
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:19,916
And they ran all over my lobby!

330
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,458
<i>♪♪</i>

331
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:24,250
[rustling]

332
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:27,000
[narrator]
<i>Was that the rhinoceros?</i>

333
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:28,500
[chattering nervously]

334
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:31,041
[suspenseful music]

335
00:15:31,125 --> 00:15:32,833
[barking]

336
00:15:32,916 --> 00:15:34,041
[giggles]

337
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:35,958
[barking]

338
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:38,166
[sighs]

339
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:40,458
[narrator] <i>Maybe what</i>
<i>George saw the night before</i>

340
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:43,416
<i>really was just a nightmare.</i>

341
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,541
[cheerful marimba music]

342
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,458
[chattering happily]

343
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:50,500
[narrator] <i>That night, George</i>
<i>wasn't going to take any chances.</i>

344
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:54,291
<i>♪♪</i>

345
00:15:54,375 --> 00:15:57,458
<i>So he had a plan.</i>

346
00:15:57,541 --> 00:16:01,041
<i>He couldn't have a nightmare</i>
<i>if he couldn't fall asleep.</i>

347
00:16:01,125 --> 00:16:02,541
<i>♪♪</i>

348
00:16:02,625 --> 00:16:05,625
<i>But a tired little monkey</i>
<i>can't stay awake forever.</i>

349
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:07,333
<i>♪♪</i>

350
00:16:07,416 --> 00:16:10,416
[musical grunting]

351
00:16:14,916 --> 00:16:17,458
<i>That did not</i>
<i>sound like the Man.</i>

352
00:16:17,541 --> 00:16:20,458
[suspenseful music]

353
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:23,500
[musical grunting continues]

354
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:26,166
[screaming]

355
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:27,416
[screaming]

356
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:29,791
[water rushing]

357
00:16:29,875 --> 00:16:31,750
[screaming]

358
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:34,208
<i>♪♪</i>

359
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:37,458
[shouting, whimpering]

360
00:16:37,541 --> 00:16:40,541
-George?
-[chattering nervously]

361
00:16:44,791 --> 00:16:47,500
[grunting]

362
00:16:48,083 --> 00:16:50,833
The rhino
was taking a shower?

363
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:54,500
[chattering earnestly]

364
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:57,500
Uh-huh,
and then the tub overflowed?

365
00:16:57,583 --> 00:17:00,458
[chattering excitedly]

366
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:03,541
Aww, it sounds like you had
another nightmare, George.

367
00:17:03,625 --> 00:17:05,875
It's over now.

368
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:08,958
[whines]

369
00:17:10,958 --> 00:17:14,540
[chattering excitedly]

370
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:17,625
That rhino really gave you
a nightmare.

371
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:19,540
I had one like that once.

372
00:17:19,625 --> 00:17:21,833
It was about a unicorn.

373
00:17:21,915 --> 00:17:23,915
 [carousel music]

374
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,333
<i>I was riding on a carousel,</i>

375
00:17:26,415 --> 00:17:30,416
<i>and suddenly, the unicorn</i>
<i>I was on took off!</i>

376
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,916
<i>I tried to hang on.</i>

377
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,583
[screaming]

378
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:36,583
[splashing]

379
00:17:36,666 --> 00:17:38,583
<i>But I couldn't.</i>

380
00:17:38,666 --> 00:17:42,416
And I landed
in a big puddle of mud.

381
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:45,916
[chattering encouragingly]

382
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,500
Thanks. Every night
for a week afterwards,

383
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:53,583
I made a wall around my bed
to keep that unicorn away.

384
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:55,791
[grunts thoughtfully]

385
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:58,583
 [playful music]

386
00:17:58,666 --> 00:18:00,625
[narrator]
<i>That night, George decided</i>

387
00:18:00,708 --> 00:18:02,541
<i>to rhino-proof his room.</i>

388
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:05,000
<i>Surely these critters</i>
<i>would protect him.</i>

389
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:10,500
<i>♪♪</i>

390
00:18:10,583 --> 00:18:13,458
<i>A tent would make</i>
<i>him feel cozy and safe.</i>

391
00:18:13,541 --> 00:18:19,458
<i>♪♪</i>

392
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:21,958
<i>No dream rhino</i>
<i>could get past all that.</i>

393
00:18:22,041 --> 00:18:25,041
[soft music]

394
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:27,958
[sighs]

395
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:34,500
<i>♪♪</i>

396
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:37,083
[sighs]

397
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:39,166
[snoring]

398
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:40,666
[screaming]

399
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:41,833
[screaming]

400
00:18:41,916 --> 00:18:43,750
[screaming]

401
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:45,833
George!

402
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:46,875
Are you okay?

403
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:49,958
[chattering nervously]

404
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:54,041
That rhino again, huh?

405
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:55,958
[whimpering]

406
00:18:56,041 --> 00:18:58,708
I think it's time
we consult the experts.

407
00:18:58,791 --> 00:19:02,083
They'll know what
to do about nightmares.

408
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:03,666
Nightmares?

409
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:07,125
No, we don't know
what to do about those.

410
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:09,125
[chatters in disbelief]

411
00:19:09,208 --> 00:19:11,583
[narrator] <i>George thought</i>
<i>scientists knew everything.</i>

412
00:19:11,666 --> 00:19:15,041
There's actually a lot
we don't know about sleep.

413
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:16,708
But we do know

414
00:19:16,791 --> 00:19:18,916
that your brain stays active
during sleep.

415
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,875
Yes, your brain uses
sleep time to repair

416
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:25,625
and grow muscles,
and fight sickness.

417
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:27,625
And it makes up stories.

418
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,125
Some of them can be scary.

419
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:31,916
[calm piano music]

420
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,625
It's time
for my afternoon nap!

421
00:19:34,708 --> 00:19:37,791
Want to see what my brain
looks like when I'm dreaming?

422
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:39,916
[chattering happily]

423
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,916
[snoring]

424
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:47,666
<i>♪♪</i>

425
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,916
He's dreaming now.

426
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,833
[coos]

427
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:53,666
Hey!

428
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:55,541
[snorting]

429
00:19:55,625 --> 00:19:58,041
Stop eating my prize!

430
00:19:58,125 --> 00:20:00,791
He has that nightmare a lot.

431
00:20:00,875 --> 00:20:04,750
He wins a big science prize,
but it's made of butterscotch

432
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,875
and the other scientists
eat it!

433
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:12,541
<i>♪♪</i>

434
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,250
Ah, oh my!

435
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:17,208
That was a doozy.

436
00:20:17,291 --> 00:20:20,500
[breathing deeply]

437
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:25,750
[chattering in curiosity]

438
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:28,708
Well, I don't know how
to stop nightmares, George.

439
00:20:28,791 --> 00:20:30,833
But when I wake up from one,

440
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:34,666
I hug my pillow
and take two deep breaths.

441
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:37,916
[breathing deeply]

442
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,000
[breathing deeply]

443
00:20:41,958 --> 00:20:44,125
Yes, just like that.

444
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:46,708
It always makes me feel better.

445
00:20:46,791 --> 00:20:49,916
[chattering happily]

446
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,125
I like to draw my nightmares
in a dream journal

447
00:20:53,208 --> 00:20:55,916
to remind myself
how silly they are.

448
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,708
You see?

449
00:20:57,791 --> 00:21:01,125
[giggling]

450
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:03,583
[chattering happily]

451
00:21:03,666 --> 00:21:05,125
You want to draw
your dreams too?

452
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:06,708
[chattering happily]

453
00:21:06,791 --> 00:21:08,958
Okay. We'll try that tonight.

454
00:21:09,041 --> 00:21:12,625
 [cheerful music]

455
00:21:12,708 --> 00:21:14,875
[giggling]

456
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:17,750
[narrator] <i>That rhino</i>
<i>didn't look so scary now.</i>

457
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:19,291
Bedtime, George.

458
00:21:19,375 --> 00:21:21,750
[chattering happily]

459
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:24,833
Is that the rhinoceros
in your nightmare?

460
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:27,333
[chattering proudly]

461
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:31,333
<i>♪♪</i>

462
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:33,208
You want to make him
your pet?

463
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:36,875
[chattering happily]

464
00:21:36,958 --> 00:21:40,666
Well, good thing
it's just a dream pet rhino.

465
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,708
We don't have the space
for a real one.

466
00:21:42,791 --> 00:21:45,166
[giggling]

467
00:21:45,250 --> 00:21:47,000
Nighty-night, George.

468
00:21:47,083 --> 00:21:50,000
[sighs]

469
00:21:50,083 --> 00:21:55,333
<i>♪♪</i>

470
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:59,333
[snorting]

471
00:21:59,416 --> 00:22:02,375
 [bombastic music]

472
00:22:02,458 --> 00:22:07,666
<i>♪♪</i>

473
00:22:07,750 --> 00:22:09,125
[shouts]

474
00:22:09,208 --> 00:22:10,791
Everything okay, George?

475
00:22:10,875 --> 00:22:13,708
[chattering nervously]

476
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:16,333
The rhino again, huh?

477
00:22:16,416 --> 00:22:18,125
You want me to sit with you?

478
00:22:18,208 --> 00:22:21,625
[grunts]

479
00:22:22,875 --> 00:22:24,375
[narrator]
<i>George was a little afraid.</i>

480
00:22:24,458 --> 00:22:27,375
<i>But he decided to do</i>
<i>what Professor Pizza did.</i>

481
00:22:27,458 --> 00:22:30,625
[breathing deeply]

482
00:22:33,416 --> 00:22:35,875
[chattering happily]

483
00:22:35,958 --> 00:22:38,333
[narrator]<i> It worked!</i>
<i>He did feel a little better.</i>

484
00:22:38,416 --> 00:22:41,041
[sighs contentedly]

485
00:22:41,125 --> 00:22:44,666
[chattering happily]

486
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:46,250
Okay.

487
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:48,250
I'm right in my room
if you need me.

488
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:52,083
<i>♪♪</i>

489
00:22:52,166 --> 00:22:54,166
[sighs]

490
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:57,166
[rhino grunting musically]

491
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:59,416
<i>♪♪</i>

492
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:02,250
[snoring]

493
00:23:03,458 --> 00:23:06,416
[fast swing music]

494
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:10,500
<i>♪♪</i>

